Program: Outlook
Title: 13/09/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00jzvft
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 14 Sep 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Aftab Jadraan tells how he went to extreme lengths to rescue his younger brother who ran away to join the now banned militant organisation Lashkar-e-Taiba in Pakistan. Also, the woman from Indonesia who gave birth to 25 children and still held down a job. And, the challenges of being a race track announcer in Kentucky. Show less